  RFC9685 [label="RFC9685
Listener Subscription for IPv6 Neighbor
Discovery Multicast and Anycast
Addresses
2024", shape=ellipse, fillcolor="#e8f0ff", tooltip="This document updates the 6LoWPAN extensions to IPv6 Neighbor Discovery (specified in RFCs 4861 and 8505) to enable a listener to subscribe to an IPv6 anycast or multicast address.  This document also updates the Routing Protocol for Low-Power and Lossy Networks (RPL) (specified in RFCs 6550 and 6553) to add a new Non-Storing multicast mode and new support for anycast addresses in Storing and Non-Storing modes.  This document extends RFC 9010 to enable a 6LoWPAN Router (6LR) to inject the anycast and multicast addresses in RPL.", style=filled, fillcolor=green, fontsize=18, penwidth=3, fontweight=bold]; 

